70b35755-8883-49ff-97ff-ca67ea5f7361.do_description: To make the output, you have to... create the grid. Then copy the original pattern onto the output grid. Next, create a mirror pattern from the original pattern underneath the original pattern. Then copy the whole original and mirror pattern to fill in the rest of the black grid.

a237c499-6208-4a7b-9601-4b1d695c6204.do_description: To make the output, you have to...if blue squares continue the pattern all the way to the end. If red do the same thing. It will be the same top and bottom.
a237c499-6208-4a7b-9601-4b1d695c6204.grid_description: The output grid size...if blue grid will be 17x9 if Red grid will be 17x13

a9cb8719-4a7c-48e7-b374-a4539fe214df.do_description: To make the output, you have to...copy the original pattern into the top of the grid, then the next few rows you create a mirror image of the first pattern using the same colors, so that it is upside down. The bottom half of the first grid is then a mirror image of the top half.  The same process is used for the second grid.
a9cb8719-4a7c-48e7-b374-a4539fe214df.grid_description: The output grid size...changes in height only. The first grid goes from four to thirteen boxes, and the second goes from three to nine boxes. The length remains the same for both grids.
a9cb8719-4a7c-48e7-b374-a4539fe214df.see_description: In the input, you should see...two input grids, one using red boxes is four boxes high and the other using blue boxes is three boxes high.

dc55677f-0003-4f7f-8d5a-66675299a2a9.do_description: To make the output, you have to...flip the pattern vertically 3 times to create a continuous pattern that is symmetrical both vertically and horizontally
dc55677f-0003-4f7f-8d5a-66675299a2a9.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same horizontally and multiplied by 3 vertically (and add 1)
